 '''''By the Rapids''''' is [[Mohawk language|Mohawk-language]] animated television show that originally aired on the [[Aboriginal Peoples Television Network]] (APTN) from 2008 to 2012.<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://kahnawakenews.com/hometown-boy-makes-good-with-by-the-rapids-p377-1.htm|publisher=Kahnawake News|title=Hometown boy makes good with By the Rapids|date=2008-06-09|website=Kahnawake News|access-date=2017-04-05}}</ref> Along with the stop-motion series ''[[Wapos Bay]]'', it was among the first Indigenous animated television series in Canada.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/2008/11/13/aboriginal_cartoon_series_5_years_in_the_making.html|title=Aboriginal cartoon series 5 years in the making|last=Szklarski|first=Cassandra|date=2008-11-13|website=Toronto Star|access-date=2017-04-05}}</ref>
 
 The series centers on Cory Littlehorn, a teenager whose family moves from the urban setting of Toronto to the small Native community where his parents grew up and the humor of day-to-day life in a small town.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Canadian television : text and context|last=Marian|first=Bredin|last2=Henderson|first2=Scott|last3=Matheson|first3=Sarah A.|isbn=129931306X|pages=88|oclc=741399601}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nativepeoples.com/Native-Peoples/November-December-2007/Indigenous-Animation-Movement-Rising/|title=Indigenous Animation Movement Rising|last=Twist|first=Kade|date=2007|work=Native Peoples Magazine|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006180037/http://www.nativepeoples.com/Native-Peoples/November-December-2007/Indigenous-Animation-Movement-Rising/|archive-date=6 October 2014|url-status=dead|quote=Lazare and Big Soul Productions have teamed up again to create a 30-minute pilot for the comedy series By the Rapids on APTN. The Mohawk-language 2D animation series is based on his hometown of Kahnawake}}</ref> It was created by [[Joseph Lazare]] who drew from his experience of moving when he was a teenager from [[Kahnawake]], a [[Mohawk people|Mohawk]] reserve outside of Montreal, to Toronto.<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=http://www.nationnews.ca/by-the-rapids-cartoon/|title=By The Rapids Cartoon|date=2008-10-25|work=The Nation: Cree News|access-date=2017-04-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180113154701/http://www.nationnews.ca/by-the-rapids-cartoon/|archive-date=2018-01-13|url-status=dead}}</ref> Lazare has stated that it was his intent to create a show that "was special to our community but wasn't neglecting people from the outside."<ref name=":1" /> Additionally, he wanted to show that his culture was filled with a variety of types of people with different lifestyles.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Thompson|first=Isha|date=2009-11-01|title=Two old friends make up a family of characters|url=http://www.ammsa.com/publications/windspeaker|journal=Windspeaker (Edmonton)|volume=27|pages=13|access-date=2017-05-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170508232555/http://www.ammsa.com/publications/windspeaker|archive-date=2017-05-08|url-status=dead}}</ref>